Program: Outlook
Title: Grieving Mum Fights Corruption in Honduras
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01n9gc1
Last Broadcast Date: Christmas Eve 2013
Jo Fidgen talks to Julieta Castellanos, a grieving mother who took on corruption in the Honduran police force after her son was brutally killed. We also hear from backing singer extraordinaire Darlene Love who has been called 'the most successful unknown singer in rock and roll history'. And Yinka Shonibare, the British-Nigerian artist who was paralysed at 19 tells Jo how he went on to win international acclaim. (Picture: Julieta Castellanos courtesy of Julieta Castellanos) Show less